AI Medical Diagnosis & Appointment System
Overview

This is a Flask-based web application that provides:

AI-powered medical diagnosis
Follow-up consultation system
Appointment scheduling
Hospital locator
PDF report generation
User authentication system

The system uses Google Gemini AI to analyze symptoms and generate medical insights.

Features
Authentication
User Registration & Login
Session management using Flask-Login
Email verification (optional)
AI Diagnosis
Enter symptoms → Get AI-based analysis
Uses Gemini API for:
Diagnosis
Treatment suggestions
Medications
Precautions
Fuzzy matching for known diseases
Follow-up System
Predefined disease-based questions
Dynamic follow-up for better accuracy
Consultation History
View past diagnoses
Download reports as PDF
Delete records
Chart visualization of activity
Appointment Management

Schedule appointments
View upcoming appointments
Cancel appointments

Hospital Locator
Enter city → View hospitals on map
Uses Geopy + Folium

PDF Reports
Generate downloadable consultation reports

Tech Stack
Backend: Flask
Database: SQLite (SQLAlchemy)
Authentication: Flask-Login
AI: Google Gemini API
Maps: Folium + Geopy
PDF: pdfkit
Frontend: HTML, Bootstrap

Project Structure
project/
│── app.py
│── app.db
│── requirements.txt
│── README.md
Installation
Clone the repo
git clone <repo-url>
cd project

Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt
Install wkhtmltopdf

Download and install:
https://wkhtmltopdf.org/downloads.html

Update path in code:

PDFKIT_CONFIG = pdfkit.configuration(
    wkhtmltopdf=r'YOUR_PATH_TO_WKHTMLTOPDF'
)

Run the app
python app.py

Open in browser:

http://127.0.0.1:5000
Configuration
Email Setup

Update in code:

MAIL_USERNAME = 'your.email@gmail.com'
MAIL_PASSWORD = 'your-app-password'
🤖 Gemini API Key

Replace with your key:

genai.configure(api_key="YOUR_API_KEY")

Test User

You can create a test user:

/create_test_user

Default:

Email: test@example.com
Password: password123
